50|$|In March 2002, the UN refugee agency began a <b>voluntary</b> <b>repatriation</b> {{campaign}} in Pakistan. By {{the end of}} 2002, UNHCR had repatriated 1.53 million Afghan refugees from Pakistan, including 1.4 million from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. 82% were from urban areas; only 3% were from new camps, which had been created {{in anticipation of the}} October 2001 US coalition invasion.|$|E
